\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Prompt 11.5 \'97 "Grab from Video" Feature\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 What this builds:
\f1\b0  A tool that lets users paste a TikTok or Instagram URL and automatically extracts every book mentioned in that video \'97 titles, authors, and any commentary the creator made about each book. Results are matched against our Goodreads-canonical book database and can be added to a Hotlist in one tap.\

\f0\b Where it lives in the app:
\f1\b0  A dedicated page at 
\f2\fs26 /grab
\f1\fs24  plus a persistent entry point in the navbar and homepage.\

\f0\b Insert this prompt between Prompt 11 and Prompt 12.
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Why this feature exists\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 BookTok and BookStagram creators post "stack" videos \'97 rapid-fire recommendations where they hold up 10-15 books in 60 seconds. Viewers have to pause, rewind, and manually write down titles they want to remember. This feature eliminates that entirely: paste the URL, get the book list, add them all to a Hotlist.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Architecture overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 User pastes URL\
      \uc0\u8595 \
Detect platform (TikTok / Instagram / YouTube)\
      \uc0\u8595 \
Download audio track via third-party API\
      \uc0\u8595 \
Transcribe audio \uc0\u8594  Whisper API (OpenAI)\
      \uc0\u8595 \
Extract book mentions \uc0\u8594  Claude Haiku\
      \uc0\u8595 \
Resolve each title \uc0\u8594  Goodreads canonical database\
      \uc0\u8595 \
Display matched books with creator commentary\
      \uc0\u8595 \
User selects books \uc0\u8594  Add to Hotlist\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Step 1 \'97 Third-party video API\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 We cannot download TikTok or Instagram videos directly \'97 both platforms block it. Instead use a third-party service that handles this legally.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Recommended: RapidAPI \'97 Social Media Video Downloader
\f1\b0 \
